OL,4,CUganda's capital bans street children
OL,5,Cdonations
OL,6, Uganda's capital Kampala has passed a
OL,7, law to ban giving money or food to
OL,8, children living on the streets.
OL,10,FKampala's Lord Mayor, Erias Lukwago,
OL,11,Fsaid the law aimed to curb the
OL,12,Fcommercial and sexual exploitation of
OL,13,Fchildren.
OL,15,FAccording to government estimates, as
OL,16,Fmany as 15,000 children live on the
OL,17,Fstreets in Kampala, aged from seven up
OL,18,Fto the age of 17.
